{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"slug":1,"metadata":2,"inscription":50,"license":84,"title":51},"ISic000157",{"file":1,"metadataFile":3,"htmlFile":4,"uri":5,"title":6,"status":7,"type":8,"objectType":12,"material":16,"notBefore":20,"notAfter":21,"geo":22,"facsimile":25,"country":28,"region":29,"settlement":30,"textLang":31,"place":34,"placeName":35,"keywords":39},"metadata/ISic000157.json","html/ISic000157.json","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000157","Funerary epitaph for Coponia","edited",{"_":9,"ana":10,"ref":11},"funerary","#function.funerary","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html",{"_":13,"ana":14,"ref":15},"plaque","#object.plaque","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259.html",{"_":17,"ana":18,"ref":19},"marble","#material.stone.marble","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html",150,200,[23,24],37,13,{"url":26,"desc":27},"ISic000157_tiled.tif","I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2023-07-05.","Italy","Sicily","Termini Imerese",{"_":32,"mainLang":33},"Latin","la",{"_":35,"type":36,"ref":37,"cert":38},"Thermae Himeraeae","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462513","low",[40,41,7,9,13,17,42,43,44,45,46,47,45,48,49,33],"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/isic000157","funerary epitaph for coponia","150","200","thermae himeraeae","termini imerese","italy","sicily","museo civico baldassare romano","latin",{"title":51,"body":52,"divs":53,"images":72},"ISic000157. Funerary epitaph for Coponia","  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000157_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2023-07-05.\" src=\"ISic000157_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000157.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2023-07-05.\" src=\"ISic000157-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000157_rear_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2023-07-05.\" src=\"ISic000157_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000157_rear.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2023-07-05.\" src=\"ISic000157_rear-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"edition\" lang=\"la\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>d(is) m(anibus) \u003Cbr id=\"al2\">Coponia Am-\u003Cbr id=\"al3\">[em]ta ((·)) v(ixit) ((·)) an(nis) ((·)) \u003Cspan class=\"latinnum\">L\u003C/span> ((·)) \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cp>  \u003Cspan class=\"\">\u003Cspan>Text on basis of autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>To the Shades of the Underworld. Coponia Amemta lived 50 years.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Ferrua suggests that the full restoration of the missing cognomen from lines 2-3 is Amemta, which is of Greek origin, and which is rare, but is more commonly found in the masculine form (Amemptos), deriving from the adjective commonly found in contemporary Greek funerary inscriptions in Sicily. There are two other attestations of members of the gens Coponia from Thermae Himeraeae, see \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000156\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000156\u003C/a> and \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000158\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000158\u003C/a>, and another attestation from Messana, see \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000273\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000273\u003C/a>. As Bivona (1994) stresses, the gens Coponia is represented by a handful of republican senators and one equestrian procurator of Judaea under Augustus.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> 1994.0777 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 1977.0339 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 78 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002137\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002137\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Ferrua 1941 262 no.22 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002655\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002655\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[54,57,60,63,66,69],{"id":55,"html":56},"edition","  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>d(is) m(anibus) \u003Cbr id=\"al2\">Coponia Am-\u003Cbr id=\"al3\">[em]ta ((·)) v(ixit) ((·)) an(nis) ((·)) \u003Cspan class=\"latinnum\">L\u003C/span> ((·)) \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  ",{"id":58,"html":59},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cp>  \u003Cspan class=\"\">\u003Cspan>Text on basis of autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003C/p>",{"id":61,"html":62},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>To the Shades of the Underworld. Coponia Amemta lived 50 years.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":64,"html":65},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Ferrua suggests that the full restoration of the missing cognomen from lines 2-3 is Amemta, which is of Greek origin, and which is rare, but is more commonly found in the masculine form (Amemptos), deriving from the adjective commonly found in contemporary Greek funerary inscriptions in Sicily. There are two other attestations of members of the gens Coponia from Thermae Himeraeae, see \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000156\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000156\u003C/a> and \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000158\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000158\u003C/a>, and another attestation from Messana, see \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000273\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000273\u003C/a>. As Bivona (1994) stresses, the gens Coponia is represented by a handful of republican senators and one equestrian procurator of Judaea under Augustus.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":67,"html":68},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> 1994.0777 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 1977.0339 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 78 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002137\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002137\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Ferrua 1941 262 no.22 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002655\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002655\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\